.TH "sca3000_write_event_config" 9 "sca3000_write_event_config" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sca3000_write_event_config \- simple on off control for motion detector
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sca3000_write_event_config
.BI "(struct iio_dev *indio_dev "  ","
.BI "const struct iio_chan_spec *chan "  ","
.BI "enum iio_event_type type "  ","
.BI "enum iio_event_direction dir "  ","
.BI "int state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "indio_dev" 12
IIO device instance specific structure. Data specific to this
particular driver may be accessed via iio_priv(indio_dev).
.IP "chan" 12
Description of the channel whose event we are configuring.
.IP "type" 12
The type of event.
.IP "dir" 12
The direction of the event.
.IP "state" 12
Desired state of event being configured.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is a per axis control, but enabling any will result in the
motion detector unit being enabled.
N.B. enabling motion detector stops normal data acquisition.
There is a complexity in knowing which mode to return to when
this mode is disabled.  Currently normal mode is assumed.
